WEBVTT

1
00:01:30.156 --> 00:01:33.492
Oh. my god. it's real.

2
00:01:37.664 --> 00:01:39.698
Bernie. thanks for seeing me.

3
00:01:39.700 --> 00:01:41.533
No worries. darling.

4
00:01:41.535 --> 00:01:42.801
Can I get you something?

5
00:01:42.803 --> 00:01:44.937
Shot of tequila. perhaps?

6
00:01:44.939 --> 00:01:46.105
I'm good.

7
00:01:46.107 --> 00:01:47.806
Are we alone?

8
00:01:47.808 --> 00:01:49.308
Yeah.

9
00:01:49.310 --> 00:01:51.710
Wait!

10
00:01:51.712 --> 00:01:52.845
You should put on gloves.

11
00:01:52.847 --> 00:01:55.380
The acetate's old.

12
00:01:55.382 --> 00:01:57.049
The oil from your fingers
could damage it.

13
00:01:59.018 --> 00:02:01.186
It's freezing.

14
00:02:01.188 --> 00:02:02.921
You been keeping it
in the icebox or something?

15
00:02:02.923 --> 00:02:06.225
Just run the spectrum analysis.
bernie. I need to know

16
00:02:06.227 --> 00:02:08.927
If it's genuine. and whatever
you do. don't actually...

17
00:02:08.929 --> 00:02:10.896
Listen to the damn thing.
You've made that clear.

18
00:02:17.070 --> 00:02:18.871
Promise me. bernie.

19
00:02:20.306 --> 00:02:22.875
Hear no evil. I swear.

20
00:02:22.877 --> 00:02:24.810
I'll get you when I'm done.
Now sod off. luv.

21
00:02:35.455 --> 00:02:37.890
I will be home as soon
as I can. honey.

22
00:02:37.892 --> 00:02:39.124
I love you. mommy.

23
00:02:39.126 --> 00:02:40.325
Oh.

24
00:03:02.249 --> 00:03:05.083
¶ crows

25
00:03:05.085 --> 00:03:08.654
¶ gonna fly...

26
00:03:21.167 --> 00:03:23.035
Oh!

27
00:03:30.510 --> 00:03:32.177
No!

28
00:03:32.179 --> 00:03:35.514
Don't make me do it!

29
00:04:16.289 --> 00:04:17.956
Hold it right there.

30
00:04:17.958 --> 00:04:19.391
You zed?

31
00:04:19.393 --> 00:04:20.826
John said you might show up.

32
00:04:20.828 --> 00:04:22.227
Kind of hoped you wouldn't.

33
00:04:22.229 --> 00:04:23.362
I gather that.
seeing how he didn't

34
00:04:23.364 --> 00:04:25.063
Actually give me an address.

35
00:04:25.065 --> 00:04:26.565
How did you find us?

36
00:04:28.201 --> 00:04:30.302
Not a lot of millhouses
in atlanta.

37
00:04:30.304 --> 00:04:32.371
John did say you
were persistent.

38
00:04:32.373 --> 00:04:36.375
Yeah. well. found
a place to live downtown.

39
00:04:36.377 --> 00:04:37.843
You'd better
get used to me.

40
00:04:37.845 --> 00:04:39.578
Zed... that means
zero. right?

41
00:04:39.580 --> 00:04:41.880
What kind of parents would
name their kid that?

42
00:04:41.882 --> 00:04:44.650
Who says my parents named me?

43
00:04:44.652 --> 00:04:45.917
Go on. then.

44
00:04:45.919 --> 00:04:47.919
Let's... Say hi

45
00:04:47.921 --> 00:04:49.554
To his satanic majesty.

46
00:04:49.556 --> 00:04:52.257
Hear me!

47
00:04:52.259 --> 00:04:55.360
Most unnameable of devourers!

48
00:04:55.362 --> 00:04:57.863
<i>Shmaynee la geree la geray</i>

49
00:04:57.865 --> 00:05:01.233
<i>Ohkleen...</i> He who guardeth
the eternal gateway...

50
00:05:01.235 --> 00:05:03.168
Who <i>natair yat aboola</i>

51
00:05:03.170 --> 00:05:05.003
<i>Dahba...</i>

52
00:05:05.005 --> 00:05:08.640
I seek an audience with one
in your embrace!

53
00:05:08.642 --> 00:05:09.741
What's he doing?

54
00:05:09.743 --> 00:05:10.809
He's learning a spell.

55
00:05:10.811 --> 00:05:12.110
Come on. I'll give you

56
00:05:12.112 --> 00:05:13.312
The penny tour.

57
00:05:13.314 --> 00:05:15.647
<i>Evray metah b'pee mehabbaqaq!</i>

58
00:05:15.649 --> 00:05:18.684
The mill belonged
to an old friend.

59
00:05:18.686 --> 00:05:21.086
He called it
a supernatural safe house.

60
00:05:21.088 --> 00:05:23.455
Most of the stuff here's
too dangerous

61
00:05:23.457 --> 00:05:25.057
To fall into the wrong hands.

62
00:05:27.827 --> 00:05:29.828
It didn't seem this
big on the outside.

63
00:05:29.830 --> 00:05:32.197
It's not.

64
00:05:32.199 --> 00:05:34.099
I've been measuring the rooms.

65
00:05:34.101 --> 00:05:35.967
Sometimes it's off a few inches.

66
00:05:35.969 --> 00:05:37.803
Sometimes more.

67
00:05:37.805 --> 00:05:39.271
That doesn't make any sense.

68
00:05:39.273 --> 00:05:43.041
If you're looking for sense.

69
00:05:43.043 --> 00:05:45.610
You stumbled down
the wrong rabbit hole.

70
00:05:50.016 --> 00:05:51.983
Easy. mate.

71
00:05:51.985 --> 00:05:54.786
Even I'm not ready
for that one yet.

72
00:05:56.155 --> 00:05:58.790
I think what chas
meant was. um.

73
00:05:58.792 --> 00:06:01.993
Don't go wandering around here
without a chaperone. all right?

74
00:06:04.263 --> 00:06:06.131
Right.

75
00:06:06.133 --> 00:06:08.800
Each one of these
stigmata represents

76
00:06:08.802 --> 00:06:11.203
A place where
something bad is going down.

77
00:06:11.205 --> 00:06:13.138
Supernatural brushfires.
if you will.

78
00:06:13.140 --> 00:06:16.241
Me. chas and a few others?

79
00:06:16.243 --> 00:06:18.643
We're the bucket brigade.
Is this your latest fire?

80
00:06:18.645 --> 00:06:20.312
Bernie was a friend of mine.

81
00:06:20.314 --> 00:06:21.747
No way in hell
he'd take his own life.

82
00:06:21.749 --> 00:06:22.881
Doesn't mean his death

83
00:06:22.883 --> 00:06:24.649
Was one of your stigmata.

84
00:06:24.651 --> 00:06:26.251
Bernie lived in
the windy city.

85
00:06:26.253 --> 00:06:27.886
And I don't believe
in coincidences.

86
00:06:27.888 --> 00:06:29.121
Go on then.

87
00:06:29.123 --> 00:06:30.555
See if you get a hit.

88
00:06:46.639 --> 00:06:50.142
I smell jasmine.

89
00:06:52.979 --> 00:06:55.313
She's a regular psychic
smorgasbord. this one.

90
00:06:55.315 --> 00:06:57.749
Picks up impressions
from tactile stimuli.

91
00:06:57.751 --> 00:07:00.252
Which I'm guessing is kind
of a buzzkill in the sack.

92
00:07:05.925 --> 00:07:07.092
It's cold!

93
00:07:07.094 --> 00:07:09.261
All right.

94
00:07:09.263 --> 00:07:11.096
Well. I'll let you know
if any of that pans out.

95
00:07:11.098 --> 00:07:12.431
No. no. no. no. no. no.

96
00:07:12.433 --> 00:07:15.167
You're not ducking
out on me again.

97
00:07:15.169 --> 00:07:17.169
You promised me you'd
teach me about my abilities.

98
00:07:17.171 --> 00:07:19.171
Teaching you is one thing.
Letting you ride shotgun

99
00:07:19.173 --> 00:07:21.072
On a spiritual scavenger hunt?

100
00:07:21.074 --> 00:07:22.107
That's another beast. luv.

101
00:07:22.109 --> 00:07:23.108
You said you didn't believe

102
00:07:23.110 --> 00:07:24.443
In coincidences.

103
00:07:24.445 --> 00:07:26.044
That's right.

104
00:07:26.046 --> 00:07:27.679
And I show up just
when you're planning to leave.

105
00:07:27.681 --> 00:07:29.848
This is my education.

106
00:07:29.850 --> 00:07:31.550
The cab's still down.

107
00:07:31.552 --> 00:07:32.851
It is.

108
00:07:32.853 --> 00:07:35.086
You got a car?
A truck.

109
00:07:35.088 --> 00:07:36.688
Knock yourself
out then. macduff.

110
00:07:36.690 --> 00:07:38.824
But. uh. I'm in charge
of the music. yeah?

111
00:07:41.360 --> 00:07:44.262
The girl's got skills.

112
00:07:44.264 --> 00:07:46.465
Yeah. and she's
easy on the eye.

113
00:07:46.467 --> 00:07:48.233
But?

114
00:07:48.235 --> 00:07:50.235
She showed up last
week out of nowhere.

115
00:07:50.237 --> 00:07:51.970
She may be legit.

116
00:07:51.972 --> 00:07:55.907
Or she may have more...
Unseemly motives.

117
00:07:55.909 --> 00:07:58.910
Either way. I'm best
keeping her close

118
00:07:58.912 --> 00:08:00.212
For now.

119
00:08:00.214 --> 00:08:03.548
See what you can dig
up on her. will you?

120
00:08:09.489 --> 00:08:11.056
What's in the man purse?

121
00:08:11.058 --> 00:08:12.123
Bits and bobs.

122
00:08:12.125 --> 00:08:14.059
Holy water. police scanner.

123
00:08:14.061 --> 00:08:15.660
Cemetery dirt. duct tape.

124
00:08:15.662 --> 00:08:16.895
What's this?
Oh. oh!

125
00:08:16.897 --> 00:08:17.963
Don't touch.

126
00:08:17.965 --> 00:08:19.231
These...

127
00:08:19.233 --> 00:08:20.799
Are nails from the coffin

128
00:08:20.801 --> 00:08:22.167
Of st. Padua.

129
00:08:22.169 --> 00:08:24.236
Patron of lost souls. Watch.

130
00:08:27.306 --> 00:08:29.741
The nails follow one another.

131
00:08:32.044 --> 00:08:34.212
Tuck one of these
in a bloke's pocket.

132
00:08:34.214 --> 00:08:36.081
You got yourself
a nifty tracking device.

133
00:08:36.083 --> 00:08:37.849
Now. if only I brought

134
00:08:37.851 --> 00:08:39.084
Something to get through

135
00:08:39.086 --> 00:08:40.819
That bloody door.

136
00:08:43.923 --> 00:08:46.091
Oh. my god! I'm so sorry!

137
00:08:46.093 --> 00:08:48.860
Sorry. Clumsy!
It's all right.

138
00:08:48.862 --> 00:08:49.995
Like this?

139
00:08:56.002 --> 00:08:59.004
We've got minutes at most.

140
00:09:05.177 --> 00:09:08.780
Oh. damn it. bernie.

141
00:09:08.782 --> 00:09:10.949
Look at the state of you.

142
00:09:10.951 --> 00:09:12.951
How did you two
know each other?

143
00:09:12.953 --> 00:09:16.588
Well. back in jurassic times.
I fronted a punk band

144
00:09:16.590 --> 00:09:18.023
Called mucous membrane.

145
00:09:18.025 --> 00:09:19.524
Yeah. that's right.

146
00:09:19.526 --> 00:09:22.327
I wasn't always an
upstanding warlock.

147
00:09:22.329 --> 00:09:25.530
Bernie here produced our
first and only record.

148
00:09:25.532 --> 00:09:27.499
He tried his best. but...

149
00:09:27.501 --> 00:09:29.534
To tell you the truth. we
were just a bunch of wankers

150
00:09:29.536 --> 00:09:31.937
Trying to get laid.
And here we are.

151
00:09:31.939 --> 00:09:35.140
Reunited for one
final comeback tour.

152
00:09:35.142 --> 00:09:37.042
Courtesy of...

153
00:09:37.044 --> 00:09:38.276
This!

154
00:09:38.278 --> 00:09:40.445
Hand of glory.

155
00:09:40.447 --> 00:09:42.781
You take the left hand of
a man that's been hanged.

156
00:09:42.783 --> 00:09:45.150
Pickle it in amniotic
fluid for seven years.

157
00:09:45.152 --> 00:09:47.485
Say the right incantation.
and the dead will rise

158
00:09:47.487 --> 00:09:49.387
For as long as
the candles burn.

159
00:09:49.389 --> 00:09:50.488
Here.

160
00:09:50.490 --> 00:09:52.357
Empty this on the floor.

161
00:09:52.359 --> 00:09:55.360
Okay.

162
00:10:03.703 --> 00:10:05.904
Hear me. most unnameable

163
00:10:05.906 --> 00:10:07.672
Of devourers...

164
00:10:07.674 --> 00:10:09.641
He who guardeth

165
00:10:09.643 --> 00:10:12.310
The golden gateway...

166
00:10:12.312 --> 00:10:15.814
I seek an audience
with one in your embrace.

167
00:10:20.186 --> 00:10:21.987
Come on. old sod.

168
00:10:46.712 --> 00:10:48.680
Hold this. Bernie.
bernie! It's john.

169
00:10:48.682 --> 00:10:50.115
Who did this to you?

170
00:10:50.117 --> 00:10:51.249
The voice!

171
00:10:51.251 --> 00:10:53.752
My god!

172
00:10:53.754 --> 00:10:55.920
The voice.

173
00:10:55.922 --> 00:10:57.689
I-I don't understand. bernie.
I don't understand.

174
00:10:57.691 --> 00:10:59.491
On the acetate.

175
00:10:59.493 --> 00:11:01.526
So cold.
No. no. Bring
the hand closer!

176
00:11:02.662 --> 00:11:04.829
Come on. bernie.
don't leave me.

177
00:11:04.831 --> 00:11:06.531
Give me something else.
give me something else. bernie.

178
00:11:06.533 --> 00:11:08.133
Come on.

179
00:11:08.135 --> 00:11:09.734
Moonrise.

180
00:11:17.977 --> 00:11:20.445
Rest in peace. mate.

181
00:11:25.518 --> 00:11:26.518
Are you okay?

182
00:11:26.520 --> 00:11:27.652
I'm just fine. luv.

183
00:11:27.654 --> 00:11:28.887
Just forced one
of my old friends

184
00:11:28.889 --> 00:11:30.321
To relive the worst moment
of his life.

185
00:11:30.323 --> 00:11:31.556
But I'm just fine.

186
00:11:31.558 --> 00:11:33.725
You said that every spell
had its price.

187
00:11:33.727 --> 00:11:35.126
What did
this one cost?

188
00:11:35.128 --> 00:11:36.294
My own mortality.

189
00:11:36.296 --> 00:11:38.363
A few days' worth.

190
00:11:38.365 --> 00:11:41.399
Kind of like
a reverse mortgage.

191
00:11:41.401 --> 00:11:42.634
You do that a lot?

192
00:11:42.636 --> 00:11:44.135
I do what it takes.

193
00:11:44.137 --> 00:11:47.639
Right. we need to find
a library to follow up

194
00:11:47.641 --> 00:11:48.873
On some of
bernie's leads.

195
00:11:48.875 --> 00:11:52.243
A voice. an acetate.
and. uh...

196
00:11:52.245 --> 00:11:54.813
"moonrise." whatever
the bloody hell that means.

197
00:11:54.815 --> 00:11:56.648
Well. my guess is
moonrise records.

198
00:11:56.650 --> 00:11:58.083
See google right here?

199
00:11:58.085 --> 00:12:00.085
Well. bernie was in
the music business.

200
00:12:00.087 --> 00:12:02.053
And back in
the 1930s.

201
00:12:02.055 --> 00:12:03.988
There was a blues record label
by the name of "moonrise."

202
00:12:03.990 --> 00:12:05.990
You don't say.

203
00:12:05.992 --> 00:12:08.159
The owner. marcus mooney.
he's still alive.

204
00:12:08.161 --> 00:12:10.361
We could go pay
him a visit.

205
00:12:36.422 --> 00:12:38.256
Mom?

206
00:12:39.459 --> 00:12:40.859
What are you doing?

207
00:12:40.861 --> 00:12:42.861
Nothing.

208
00:12:42.863 --> 00:12:44.863
I-I was just...

209
00:12:44.865 --> 00:12:46.698
Why are you up?

210
00:12:46.700 --> 00:12:48.299
I had a nightmare.

211
00:12:48.301 --> 00:12:50.835
Aw. baby.

212
00:12:52.872 --> 00:12:55.540
Someone was trying
to take you away from me.

213
00:12:55.542 --> 00:12:57.175
I'm not going anywhere. julilah.

214
00:13:04.383 --> 00:13:05.884
Mom?

215
00:13:05.886 --> 00:13:06.918
Yeah.

216
00:13:06.920 --> 00:13:08.019
What's that?

217
00:13:21.433 --> 00:13:24.769
<i>Hi. we're here
to see marcus mooney.</i>

218
00:13:24.771 --> 00:13:26.838
Visiting hours are over.

219
00:13:28.941 --> 00:13:31.142
Health and human services.

220
00:13:31.144 --> 00:13:34.946
Now. I am sure. tammy. that you
can make an exception now.

221
00:13:34.948 --> 00:13:37.615
Room 2022.

222
00:13:37.617 --> 00:13:39.551
Thank you. now.

223
00:13:39.553 --> 00:13:40.785
That was a neat trick.

224
00:13:40.787 --> 00:13:41.953
It's not a trick.

225
00:13:41.955 --> 00:13:43.054
Magic.

226
00:13:43.056 --> 00:13:44.823
And not
the copperfield kind.

227
00:13:44.825 --> 00:13:46.558
The card's charmed.

228
00:13:46.560 --> 00:13:48.092
It's got a pretty
bloody backstory.

229
00:13:48.094 --> 00:13:49.761
But the gist
of it is...

230
00:13:49.763 --> 00:13:53.131
It takes on the appearance
of whatever its holder requires.

231
00:14:02.641 --> 00:14:05.710
Who are you?

232
00:14:05.712 --> 00:14:08.546
Friends. if you'll have us.

233
00:14:10.482 --> 00:14:11.983
You seem like a friend.

234
00:14:13.018 --> 00:14:15.019
That one's got a...

235
00:14:15.021 --> 00:14:17.522
A shadow dogging his soul.

236
00:14:17.524 --> 00:14:20.391
More than one.
marcus.

237
00:14:20.393 --> 00:14:21.926
I'm john constantine.

238
00:14:21.928 --> 00:14:23.494
I need some help.

239
00:14:23.496 --> 00:14:25.697
I'm here to ask
about the acetate.

240
00:14:25.699 --> 00:14:28.399
Lord. don't tell me
you played it.

241
00:14:28.401 --> 00:14:29.868
No.

242
00:14:29.870 --> 00:14:33.204
But a friend of mine.
he might have.

243
00:14:33.206 --> 00:14:35.440
And now he's dead.

244
00:14:35.442 --> 00:14:37.508
You care to shed some light
on the matter?

245
00:14:39.078 --> 00:14:41.246
You ever heard of...

246
00:14:41.248 --> 00:14:42.513
Willie cole?

247
00:14:42.515 --> 00:14:45.216
A memphis bluesman.

248
00:14:45.218 --> 00:14:48.786
Burned bright in the '30s. and
then just upped and vanished.

249
00:14:48.788 --> 00:14:52.590
I used to produce him.

250
00:14:53.592 --> 00:14:56.327
<i>I had an old recording studio.</i>

251
00:14:56.329 --> 00:14:58.630
I know you like to sing alone.
so I'll leave you to it.

252
00:14:58.632 --> 00:14:59.697
All right.

253
00:15:04.203 --> 00:15:09.841
<i>Willie's legend was.
he sold his soul to the devil.</i>

254
00:15:09.843 --> 00:15:13.845
Never put much stock in that.

255
00:15:13.847 --> 00:15:16.814
¶ shadows gonna rise...

256
00:15:16.816 --> 00:15:23.054
<i>Turns out. the acetate
he was working on...</i>

257
00:15:23.056 --> 00:15:26.557
<i>Recorded something
when he died.</i>

258
00:15:26.559 --> 00:15:27.825
¶ bitch dogs gonna howl...

259
00:15:27.827 --> 00:15:31.195
<i>The voice of the deceiver.</i>

260
00:15:31.197 --> 00:15:33.298
Hmm.

261
00:15:33.300 --> 00:15:35.066
That's an urban legend. mate.

262
00:15:35.068 --> 00:15:36.534
This is real.

263
00:15:38.304 --> 00:15:40.371
Hello?

264
00:15:48.682 --> 00:15:50.014
No.

265
00:15:50.016 --> 00:15:51.249
It's not my path.

266
00:15:51.251 --> 00:15:52.884
You promised!

267
00:15:53.886 --> 00:15:55.987
You promised!

268
00:16:04.463 --> 00:16:07.532
<i>Wasn't nothing left
except blood.</i>

269
00:16:09.468 --> 00:16:11.602
When I picked up the acetate.

270
00:16:11.604 --> 00:16:13.571
<i>I heard whispers.</i>

271
00:16:13.573 --> 00:16:16.007
I-I-in... In my head.

272
00:16:16.009 --> 00:16:17.842
<i>Voices...</i>

273
00:16:17.844 --> 00:16:20.345
Telling me to do
horrible things.

274
00:16:20.347 --> 00:16:23.247
A-and it was cold...

275
00:16:23.249 --> 00:16:24.449
To the touch.

276
00:16:24.451 --> 00:16:26.617
It was so cold.

277
00:16:26.619 --> 00:16:28.186
Why didn't you destroy it?

278
00:16:28.188 --> 00:16:30.021
Well. don't you
think I tried?

279
00:16:30.023 --> 00:16:31.823
I... Nothing worked.

280
00:16:31.825 --> 00:16:35.093
So I buried it. I...

281
00:16:35.095 --> 00:16:38.329
<i>Hid it. I sealed it up
inside a wall.</i>

282
00:16:38.331 --> 00:16:40.264
And I prayed.

283
00:16:40.266 --> 00:16:43.201
Any idea how bernie
came across it?

284
00:16:43.203 --> 00:16:44.669
Private investigator.

285
00:16:44.671 --> 00:16:47.305
Come to see me just last week.

286
00:16:47.307 --> 00:16:49.707
Knew about the legend.

287
00:16:49.709 --> 00:16:52.276
Wanted to buy the acetate.

288
00:16:52.278 --> 00:16:54.012
The private investigator.

289
00:16:54.014 --> 00:16:56.280
He didn't happen to mention
who he worked for. did he?

290
00:16:56.282 --> 00:16:57.615
Oh. no.

291
00:16:57.617 --> 00:17:00.918
But I saw a name on the check.

292
00:17:00.920 --> 00:17:02.987
"fell."

293
00:17:07.026 --> 00:17:09.260
You did very good. marcus.

294
00:17:09.262 --> 00:17:13.364
I think it's time for me...

295
00:17:13.366 --> 00:17:15.933
To go to my reward.

296
00:17:15.935 --> 00:17:17.935
Why do you say that?

297
00:17:17.937 --> 00:17:21.539
I see an angel
standing there.

298
00:17:25.811 --> 00:17:27.378
Nurse!

299
00:17:38.057 --> 00:17:40.658
Shh...

300
00:17:59.978 --> 00:18:03.581
You recognized that name
marcus mentioned. didn't you?

301
00:18:03.583 --> 00:18:06.084
Fell.

302
00:18:06.086 --> 00:18:08.553
You remember I said that
bernie found some real stars?

303
00:18:08.555 --> 00:18:10.054
Yeah.

304
00:18:10.056 --> 00:18:12.890
Well. the brightest was
a metalhead named ian fell.

305
00:18:12.892 --> 00:18:14.859
Sold his soul.

306
00:18:14.861 --> 00:18:16.427
You don't seem surprised
at the idea

307
00:18:16.429 --> 00:18:18.563
Of old scratch
bartering for souls.

308
00:18:18.565 --> 00:18:21.732
There's one thing
I never understood is

309
00:18:21.734 --> 00:18:23.935
Why he even wants our souls.

310
00:18:23.937 --> 00:18:27.171
The devil used to be an angel.

311
00:18:27.173 --> 00:18:29.774
That's why he's called
the "first of the fallen."

312
00:18:29.776 --> 00:18:32.510
You ask a holy type.
and they'll tell you...

313
00:18:32.512 --> 00:18:35.847
<i>The soul is the purest
expression of god's love.</i>

314
00:18:35.849 --> 00:18:37.949
The spark of creation.

315
00:18:39.618 --> 00:18:44.622
<i>Every time the first takes
a soul. he's exacting revenge.</i>

316
00:18:44.624 --> 00:18:47.658
<i>Paying back the almighty
for casting him out.</i>

317
00:18:53.465 --> 00:18:55.633
I do want to hear you.

318
00:18:55.635 --> 00:18:57.168
I do.

319
00:19:09.715 --> 00:19:10.948
What are you doing?

320
00:19:10.950 --> 00:19:12.183
I'm breaking
into the mansion.

321
00:19:12.185 --> 00:19:13.251
Isn't that illegal?

322
00:19:15.187 --> 00:19:16.888
Almost everything I do is. luv.

323
00:19:16.890 --> 00:19:18.456
Come on.

324
00:19:29.369 --> 00:19:32.303
There he is. that smug tosser.

325
00:19:42.814 --> 00:19:44.182
Whoa. whoa.
whoa. whoa!

326
00:19:44.184 --> 00:19:45.184
Don't shout!

327
00:19:45.185 --> 00:19:46.250
And don't squirm.

328
00:19:46.252 --> 00:19:47.485
How did bernie get the acetate?

329
00:19:47.487 --> 00:19:49.086
Acet...?

330
00:19:49.088 --> 00:19:51.756
Bernie was a
friend. ian.

331
00:19:51.758 --> 00:19:53.691
He was a friend.

332
00:19:53.693 --> 00:19:56.527
And if he died as a result
of a deal that you made.

333
00:19:56.529 --> 00:19:58.095
There's gonna be retribution.

334
00:19:58.097 --> 00:20:00.731
Look. man. I don't know anything
about any deal!

335
00:20:00.733 --> 00:20:02.333
A no-talent hack

336
00:20:02.335 --> 00:20:05.002
Turns overnight sensation.
and you're telling me

337
00:20:05.004 --> 00:20:06.504
That you didn't take a shortcut.

338
00:20:06.506 --> 00:20:08.172
Hey. john. something's going on.

339
00:20:08.174 --> 00:20:09.907
I keep smelling jasmine.

340
00:20:09.909 --> 00:20:12.577
Now. this guy is backing out
of a deal. and people are dying.

341
00:20:12.579 --> 00:20:14.245
And you need to own up to it.

342
00:20:14.247 --> 00:20:15.379
He can't.

343
00:20:16.849 --> 00:20:18.015
He didn't
make the deal.

344
00:20:19.051 --> 00:20:20.418
I did.

345
00:20:20.420 --> 00:20:22.553
Jasmine fell.

346
00:20:22.555 --> 00:20:25.790
Off-key backup singer
and loyal spouse.

347
00:20:25.792 --> 00:20:27.558
Ain't love grand?

348
00:20:27.560 --> 00:20:30.094
Jasmine. do we know
these people?

349
00:20:30.096 --> 00:20:31.729
We're not
here to hurt you.

350
00:20:31.731 --> 00:20:33.130
Don't be so sure.

351
00:20:33.132 --> 00:20:35.633
The night's still young.
and bernie's still dead.

352
00:20:35.635 --> 00:20:36.867
This is a nightmare.

353
00:20:36.869 --> 00:20:38.369
Just tell me what's
going on. please.

354
00:20:38.371 --> 00:20:39.604
Yeah. tell him.

355
00:20:39.606 --> 00:20:41.305
Tell him how you entered
into a contract

356
00:20:41.307 --> 00:20:42.640
You're now trying to break

357
00:20:42.642 --> 00:20:44.108
At the cost
of other people's lives.

358
00:20:44.110 --> 00:20:45.710
Just so you could
climb the charts.

359
00:20:45.712 --> 00:20:47.878
That's not it.
No. of course.

360
00:20:47.880 --> 00:20:50.214
Because the money really hurt
your lifestyle. didn't it?

361
00:20:50.216 --> 00:20:52.116
The mega mansion.
the shiny clothes.

362
00:20:52.118 --> 00:20:54.619
Did you even bother to check
the price tag of those shoes?

363
00:20:54.621 --> 00:20:56.320
Ian was dying.

364
00:20:56.322 --> 00:20:57.622
He had cancer.

365
00:21:01.893 --> 00:21:03.561
I didn't see that one coming.

366
00:21:05.897 --> 00:21:08.399
You sacrificed your
soul for his life.

367
00:21:11.036 --> 00:21:13.037
Why don't you show him
the contract. luv?

368
00:21:24.550 --> 00:21:27.685
Do you remember your
first day in the hospital?

369
00:21:27.687 --> 00:21:31.022
They said you had
a month. maybe two.

370
00:21:31.024 --> 00:21:33.691
This man came to me
in the waiting room that night.

371
00:21:33.693 --> 00:21:35.559
He told me his name was anton.

372
00:21:35.561 --> 00:21:37.161
Sounds like a soul broker.

373
00:21:37.163 --> 00:21:39.430
They troll hospitals
for the dying.

374
00:21:39.432 --> 00:21:42.633
I didn't even think it was real.

375
00:21:42.635 --> 00:21:44.135
But I signed it.

376
00:21:44.137 --> 00:21:46.304
Then you went into
total remission.

377
00:21:46.306 --> 00:21:48.773
May I?

378
00:21:48.775 --> 00:21:50.174
Etruscan rune.

379
00:21:50.176 --> 00:21:51.442
This anton...

380
00:21:51.444 --> 00:21:53.144
He may have been a skeevy bloke.

381
00:21:53.146 --> 00:21:55.946
But he had a toe in
the nether realm. all right.

382
00:21:55.948 --> 00:21:58.949
Take a look.

383
00:21:58.951 --> 00:22:00.184
Anton said

384
00:22:00.186 --> 00:22:01.652
When the last words faded.

385
00:22:01.654 --> 00:22:03.788
The first of the fallen
would return to claim

386
00:22:03.790 --> 00:22:05.256
His prize.

387
00:22:05.258 --> 00:22:08.459
So. why try and break
the deal. jasmine?

388
00:22:08.461 --> 00:22:09.694
It wasn't my idea.

389
00:22:09.696 --> 00:22:11.095
Anton got back in touch.

390
00:22:11.097 --> 00:22:12.530
He told me he could
trade my soul back

391
00:22:12.532 --> 00:22:14.465
For the
acetate.

392
00:22:14.467 --> 00:22:16.300
Soul brokers never break a deal.

393
00:22:16.302 --> 00:22:18.969
They lose their right of parley
with the underworld.

394
00:22:18.971 --> 00:22:21.205
Something here
doesn't add up.

395
00:22:21.207 --> 00:22:23.174
So what did
this. uh.

396
00:22:23.176 --> 00:22:24.975
Anton want
you to do?

397
00:22:24.977 --> 00:22:27.278
He wanted me to hunt
down the acetate.

398
00:22:27.280 --> 00:22:29.814
He knew you were a
rock star with money

399
00:22:29.816 --> 00:22:31.215
And endless resources.

400
00:22:31.217 --> 00:22:32.650
And motivation.

401
00:22:32.652 --> 00:22:34.719
This. uh. anton...

402
00:22:34.721 --> 00:22:37.355
When did he expect to lay
his hands on the acetate?

403
00:22:37.357 --> 00:22:40.057
I'm supposed to take
it to him tonight.

404
00:22:40.059 --> 00:22:43.060
He texted me
an address.

405
00:22:43.062 --> 00:22:45.629
Let me take care
of that for you.

406
00:22:45.631 --> 00:22:48.132
I'm your best shot
at ending this nightmare.

407
00:22:50.569 --> 00:22:52.002
Give us a hug. then.

408
00:22:59.311 --> 00:23:00.644
Thank
you.

409
00:23:22.068 --> 00:23:27.772
¶ crows gonna fly

410
00:23:27.774 --> 00:23:30.408
¶ bitch dogs gonna howl

411
00:23:30.410 --> 00:23:31.442
What's that music?

412
00:23:31.444 --> 00:23:34.145
Oh. my god.
Julilah!

413
00:23:34.147 --> 00:23:36.614
¶ reaper man gonna come...
Julilah!

414
00:23:36.616 --> 00:23:39.150
Get away from it!
Get away from it!
Get away from it!

415
00:23:39.152 --> 00:23:40.284
Oh. my god.

416
00:23:40.286 --> 00:23:41.585
Is she okay?

417
00:23:41.587 --> 00:23:43.521
Look at me. julilah.
Is she okay. jas?

418
00:23:43.523 --> 00:23:45.923
Yeah. yeah.
I think she's okay.

419
00:23:45.925 --> 00:23:47.925
Baby...

420
00:23:49.729 --> 00:23:51.695
Open your heart to the lord

421
00:23:51.697 --> 00:23:54.665
And let yourself be healed.

422
00:23:54.667 --> 00:23:57.067
For god's presence inside you.

423
00:23:57.069 --> 00:23:59.203
In your mind. body and soul...

424
00:23:59.205 --> 00:24:02.740
God has spoken to us
through the scriptures.

425
00:24:02.742 --> 00:24:05.209
We must share the gospel

426
00:24:05.211 --> 00:24:06.911
And spread god's wisdom

427
00:24:06.913 --> 00:24:08.746
To those who have never heard

428
00:24:08.748 --> 00:24:11.182
The word of the lord.

429
00:24:11.184 --> 00:24:12.850
Name it and claim it!

430
00:24:12.852 --> 00:24:15.252
Ah. you must
be anton.

431
00:24:15.254 --> 00:24:17.021
Who are you?

432
00:24:17.023 --> 00:24:19.190
Someone who knows
that soul brokers

433
00:24:19.192 --> 00:24:20.925
Are ambulance
chasers.

434
00:24:20.927 --> 00:24:22.059
Not original thinkers.

435
00:24:22.061 --> 00:24:23.093
Save a human soul?

436
00:24:23.095 --> 00:24:25.362
A wall-licker like you

437
00:24:25.364 --> 00:24:26.964
Don't have the power.

438
00:24:26.966 --> 00:24:29.600
So... What kind of a con

439
00:24:29.602 --> 00:24:31.068
Are you running
on the lady?

440
00:24:31.070 --> 00:24:32.369
There's no con.

441
00:24:32.371 --> 00:24:33.604
Okay?

442
00:24:33.606 --> 00:24:34.872
Just give me the acetate.

443
00:24:34.874 --> 00:24:36.106
I'll give her what she wants.

444
00:24:36.108 --> 00:24:38.075
She wants

445
00:24:38.077 --> 00:24:40.444
Her soul.

446
00:24:40.446 --> 00:24:42.379
And it's not
yours to give.

447
00:24:42.381 --> 00:24:43.647
You traded it

448
00:24:43.649 --> 00:24:45.316
20 years ago
for ian fell's life.

449
00:24:45.318 --> 00:24:47.151
No. don't say his name!
Why not?

450
00:24:47.153 --> 00:24:49.353
You just blew
my deal!

451
00:25:01.032 --> 00:25:04.368
I should've known that
you were behind this.

452
00:25:04.370 --> 00:25:06.971
Papa midnite.

453
00:25:06.973 --> 00:25:08.472
All right.

454
00:25:20.653 --> 00:25:23.120
So... Ian fell.

455
00:25:24.256 --> 00:25:25.723
Thank you. constantine.

456
00:25:25.725 --> 00:25:28.826
At least I know where
to find the acetate now.

457
00:25:28.828 --> 00:25:30.895
Papa midnite.

458
00:25:33.164 --> 00:25:36.767
I didn't take you for a fan
of religious broadcasting.

459
00:25:36.769 --> 00:25:38.168
Unless there's a voodoo channel

460
00:25:38.170 --> 00:25:40.437
I'm missing from
my basic cable package.

461
00:25:40.439 --> 00:25:42.006
On the contrary.

462
00:25:42.008 --> 00:25:44.341
There's a lot these learned men
can teach me.

463
00:25:44.343 --> 00:25:45.776
Like what?

464
00:25:45.778 --> 00:25:47.177
How to trick
a desperate woman

465
00:25:47.179 --> 00:25:48.579
Into using all
her resources

466
00:25:48.581 --> 00:25:50.648
To obtain a deadly
artifact for you?

467
00:25:50.650 --> 00:25:51.982
You know.

468
00:25:51.984 --> 00:25:53.684
That recording. in your hands.

469
00:25:53.686 --> 00:25:55.819
Gives you more power
than I'm comfortable with. mate.

470
00:25:55.821 --> 00:25:58.122
Name it and claim it.

471
00:25:58.124 --> 00:25:59.456
Come again?

472
00:25:59.458 --> 00:26:01.692
It's the basic building block

473
00:26:01.694 --> 00:26:03.427
Of televangelism.

474
00:26:03.429 --> 00:26:05.963
There are promises out there

475
00:26:05.965 --> 00:26:07.364
Waiting for us.

476
00:26:07.366 --> 00:26:09.500
If we only have the courage

477
00:26:09.502 --> 00:26:12.169
To name them and claim them.

478
00:26:12.171 --> 00:26:14.705
That's exactly the kind
of backward thinking

479
00:26:14.707 --> 00:26:16.540
I'd expect from a cheating.

480
00:26:16.542 --> 00:26:18.375
Drug-dealing voodoo priest
like...

481
00:26:31.389 --> 00:26:32.556
Aah!

482
00:26:40.098 --> 00:26:42.533
They tell me this place
used to flourish.

483
00:26:42.535 --> 00:26:43.767
Busy factories

484
00:26:43.769 --> 00:26:45.369
Making things.

485
00:26:45.371 --> 00:26:46.737
Workers
scurrying...

486
00:26:46.739 --> 00:26:51.208
Now it's a concrete graveyard.

487
00:26:51.210 --> 00:26:53.043
All this just to get me alone?

488
00:26:53.045 --> 00:26:54.578
I'm flattered.

489
00:26:54.580 --> 00:26:56.413
But you're gonna have to
respect my boundaries.

490
00:26:56.415 --> 00:26:59.249
I don't do zip ties
without a safe word.

491
00:26:59.251 --> 00:27:00.484
Made of copper.

492
00:27:00.486 --> 00:27:01.785
More than effective

493
00:27:01.787 --> 00:27:03.721
Against your
mail-order magic.

494
00:27:04.923 --> 00:27:07.324
My men are unburdening ian fell

495
00:27:07.326 --> 00:27:08.993
Of his problem as we speak.

496
00:27:08.995 --> 00:27:10.995
Thanks to you.
constantine.

497
00:27:10.997 --> 00:27:12.963
What do you want
with the acetate. midnite?

498
00:27:12.965 --> 00:27:14.798
There's no money it in.

499
00:27:14.800 --> 00:27:16.900
It's an insurance policy.

500
00:27:16.902 --> 00:27:18.602
A get-out-of-hell-free card.

501
00:27:18.604 --> 00:27:21.972
Don't tell me
that's not why you're after it.

502
00:27:21.974 --> 00:27:24.174
You know. I lied.

503
00:27:24.176 --> 00:27:25.442
About ian fell.

504
00:27:25.444 --> 00:27:27.478
For you. lying is easy.

505
00:27:27.480 --> 00:27:30.147
You've been at it so long.

506
00:27:30.149 --> 00:27:32.282
You've forgotten what it's like
to work hard

507
00:27:32.284 --> 00:27:34.151
- For something.
- Ooh....

508
00:27:34.153 --> 00:27:36.186
Ooh... What is that?

509
00:27:36.188 --> 00:27:38.188
Heparin.

510
00:27:38.190 --> 00:27:40.157
An anticoagulant.

511
00:27:51.269 --> 00:27:53.537
You'll have
four hours.

512
00:27:53.539 --> 00:27:55.372
That's if you stay very still

513
00:27:55.374 --> 00:27:57.775
And say your prayers.

514
00:27:57.777 --> 00:27:59.043
A slow death.

515
00:27:59.045 --> 00:28:00.778
But not too slow.
Is that it?

516
00:28:00.780 --> 00:28:02.780
If my two associates
don't return

517
00:28:02.782 --> 00:28:04.515
From fell's with
the acetate.

518
00:28:04.517 --> 00:28:06.450
I want to be able to come back

519
00:28:06.452 --> 00:28:08.185
And question you more...

520
00:28:08.187 --> 00:28:11.088
Aggressively.

521
00:28:11.090 --> 00:28:13.390
Oh...

522
00:28:13.392 --> 00:28:15.459
I always took you for a...

523
00:28:15.461 --> 00:28:17.428
A voodoo priest with a...

524
00:28:17.430 --> 00:28:18.862
A flair for the dramatic.

525
00:28:18.864 --> 00:28:20.264
But a cold-blooded
killer?

526
00:28:20.266 --> 00:28:22.032
I do what's needed.

527
00:28:22.034 --> 00:28:24.234
But I don't need to darken
my soul tonight.

528
00:28:24.236 --> 00:28:27.204
Not with the situation
firmly in hand.

529
00:28:27.206 --> 00:28:30.808
A pharmaceutical dose
of vitamin k.

530
00:28:30.810 --> 00:28:33.811
This will stop the bleeding...

531
00:28:33.813 --> 00:28:35.946
If you can
get to it.

532
00:28:35.948 --> 00:28:37.514
Consider it a show of

533
00:28:37.516 --> 00:28:39.616
Professional
respect.

534
00:28:39.618 --> 00:28:42.052
If you live.
you have worked

535
00:28:42.054 --> 00:28:44.722
Very hard indeed.

536
00:28:44.724 --> 00:28:46.323
